<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 21-SI SERIES - BEARING REPLACEMENT - DE FRAME BEARING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="1">
        <title>DE FRAME BEARING</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801717">Figure 17</hotlnk>
                for Item numbers in parentheses.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0801717" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0801717" filename="../figg08/G0801717.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>DE Frame and Components</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEX WRENCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. COMMON WRENCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SHAFT NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. PULLEY</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. FAN</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. ROTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. BEARING RETAINER PLATE ATTACHING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. RETAINER PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. DE FRAME BEARING</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. DE FRAME</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <para>Hold the DE frame (Item 11) and spin rotor (Item 7) by hand to see that it spins freely in ball
                bearing (Item 10). Bearing is permanently lubricated; do not add grease. If movement is rough or wobbly,
                replace DE bearing.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove pulley nut (Item 5) by placing hex wrench (Item 1) in end of shaft to hold while
                    removing nut (Item 3). If hex wrench is not available, wrap rotor in shop cloth and place in vise.
                    Tighten just enough to hold while removing pulley nut.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift shaft nut washer (Item 4), pulley (Item 5), and fan (Item 6) from rotor shaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull rotor (Item 7) thru DE bearing (Item 10).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove three bearing retainer plate attaching screws (Item 8) from bearing retainer
                    plate (Item 9) in DE frame (Item 11).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bearing retainer plate (Item 11) and DE frame bearing (Item 10).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <para>Place new bearing (Item 10) and bearing retainer plate (Item 9) in DE frame (Item 11). Install 3
                attaching screws (Item 8). Tighten the retainer plate attaching screws to 26 in-lb (3.0 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
